snippet.textDisplay:
Dear Nvidia, i am one of those gamers still waiting for GPU availability. I care most about traditional rasterization, ray tracing is not for me yet. But I do like DLSS... So I'm probably still buying Nvidia if I have to choose between 3080 and 6800xt at similar price. 

Eventually I'll switch to AMD on RDNA 3 or whatever in the future because I can't afford Nvidia's enthusiast class GPU prices. I respect myself too much to be taken advantage of again and again.

Weeks ago i would have bought AMD hands down but since there hasn't been any stock, i bought a 4k 120hz tv and now I realize how much more necessary DLSS would be.

Had it not been for 4k, i still think 1440p 165hz gaming is still the best sweet spot. I still don't care about RTX until it completely blows me away. I'd rather keep my FPS than lose it.

snippet.textDisplay:
To be fair, Hardware Unboxed has never focused too much on raytracing, usually unable to see the benefits or simply prefer the frame rate.

Just recently they mentioned the performance drop for slightly better shadows in Cold War, and while they are right, those shadows work so well their existence becomes subtle.  I'd much rather have shadows and GI over reflections any day.

Edit: Oh and this is nothing against Hardware Unboxed, they have some of the best best reviews out there. I just don't usually like their takes on raytracing, especially when price to performance gets brought up with raytracing being left out.
